{"id":6078,"date":"2015-06-11T07:00:22","date_gmt":"2015-06-11T13:00:22","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/?p=6078"},"modified":"2018-12-08T11:23:44","modified_gmt":"2018-12-08T18:23:44","slug":"succulents-in-a-bird-bath","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/succulents-in-a-bird-bath\/","title":{"rendered":"How to Plant Succulents in a bird bath"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p><em>If you have an bird bath that is broken, doesn't usually have water in it, or just needs some jazzing up, try planting succulents in it!\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n<p>My mom has had this bird bath in her garden for a long time. Last fall I thought it would be fun to plant some succulents around the base.<\/p>\n<p>I didn't do a great job planting them and, since they only get watered when it rains, some of them died. Quite a few survived though and they are looking good.<\/p>\n<p>I've always thought it would be fun to fill a bird bath with succulents and have seen some beautiful photos of them. So, I asked if she'd let me fill the bird bath with succulents and she said yes!<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_6082\" style=\"width: 595px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-6082\" class=\"wp-image-6082 size-large\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/This-bird-bath-filled-with-succulents-is-gorgeous-I-want-to-do-this-in-my-garden-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"This bird bath filled with succulents is gorgeous! I want to do this in my garden\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-6082\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_semps&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Fcold-hardy-sempervivums%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sempervivums<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_sedums&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Fcold-hardy-sedums%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sedums<\/a><\/p><\/div>\n<p>This was a really fun project and I'm happy with how it turned out. The only things that made it difficult were drilling a hole in the bird bath and being outside for a while in the hot afternoon sun (probably not the best time to plant).<\/p>\n<p>Here's what you'll need for this project:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>An empty bird bath (mine is similar to <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1Qb8HUR\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">this one<\/a>)<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/Succulent_Soil_sas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Succulent soil<\/a>\u00a0(see <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/tips-planting-succulents-bird-bath\/\">this post<\/a> for why a different soil may be better)<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_semps&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Fcold-hardy-sempervivums%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sempervivums<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_sedums&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Fcold-hardy-sedums%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sedums<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1TYZD4y\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Drill<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1SZVJrP\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Diamond tip drill bit<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Here's a step by step of what I did to fill up this beauty!<\/p>\n<p>First I drilled a hole in the bottom of the <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1Qb8HUR\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">bird bath<\/a> for drainage. I used a diamond tip <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1SZVJrP\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">drill bit<\/a>. If you haven't done this before, here is a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=SFBIzAdMqoU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">video tutorial<\/a> to show you how.<\/p>\n<p>Start by filling the bird bath with a little bit of water to keep the surface and drill bit wet. Start at an angle and straighten out the drill bit as you get deeper.<\/p>\n<p>This was by far the hardest part of planting this bird bath. Having at least one drainage hole is crucial.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6090\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Drill-a-hole-in-your-bird-bath-to-provide-proper-drainage-for-your-succulents-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"Drill a hole in your bird bath to provide proper drainage for your succulents\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6086\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/A-drainage-hole-in-your-birdbath-will-prevent-the-succulents-from-rotting-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"A drainage hole in your birdbath will prevent the succulents from rotting\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I only did one hole because the bird bath is so shallow and will\u00a0dry out relatively fast. The one hole will prevent water from pooling for too\u00a0long.<\/p>\n<p>After the drainage hole was in I added the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/Succulent_Soil_sas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">soil<\/a>. I recommend mounding the soil in the middle to create some height.<\/p>\n<p>Since I'm using mostly cold hardy\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_semps&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Fcold-hardy-sempervivums%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sempervivums<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_sedums&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Fcold-hardy-sedums%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sedums<\/a>\u00a0(which don't get very tall) I didn't want the design to be flat. Mounding the soil allowed me to create a nice hill of succulents.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6088\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Create-a-mound-of-soil-before-adding-succulents-to-your-birdbath-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"Create a mound of soil before adding succulents to your birdbath\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I purchased a larger <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_semps2&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FSucculentBeauties%2Fsearch%3Fsearch_query%3Dsempervivum%26order%3Ddate_desc%26view_type%3Dgallery%26ref%3Dshop_search\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sempervivum<\/a> to be the focal point. I bought it locally so I was able to pick out a large specimen surrounded by lots of chicks.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6083\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Use-a-large-succulent-to-create-a-focal-point-in-your-bird-bath-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"Use a large succulent to create a focal point in your bird bath\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p>After that I added in some cold hardy <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_sedums2&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F124557625%2Fsmall-sedum-angelicum-cluster%3Fref%3Dshop_home_active_3%26ga_search_query%3Dsedum\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sedums<\/a> around the edges.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6087\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Add-sedums-to-fill-in-and-contrast-with-the-sempervivums-in-your-bird-bath-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"Add sedums to fill in and contrast with the sempervivums in your bird bath\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I filled in most of the rest with more Sempervivums.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6085\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Use-sempervivusms-and-sedums-to-create-a-cold-hardy-succulent-filled-bird-bath-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"Use sempervivusms and sedums to create a cold hardy succulent filled bird bath\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Once I had all of my plants in, I covered the exposed soil with a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/bonsai_succulent_top_dressingsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">top dressing<\/a> to finish it off. I always like adding a top dressing, but this definitely contributed\u00a0to the composition and helped the design look complete.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6084\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Use-decorative-rocks-to-cover-the-soil-in-your-succulent-bird-bath-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"Use decorative rocks to cover the soil in your succulent bird bath\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I made sure to fill the bird bath with cold hardy <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_semps&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FSucculentBeauties%2Fsearch%3Fsearch_query%3Dsempervivum%26order%3Ddate_desc%26view_type%3Dgallery%26ref%3Dshop_search\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sempervivums<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=birdbath_sedums&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F124557625%2Fsmall-sedum-angelicum-cluster%3Fref%3Dshop_home_active_3%26ga_search_query%3Dsedum\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sedums<\/a>\u00a0since my parents live in a Zone 5 climate. The winters get very cold and most other succulents won't survive.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6089\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Create-a-stunning-piece-of-garden-decor-by-filling-a-bird-bath-with-cold-hardy-succulents-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Create a stunning piece of garden decor by filling a bird bath with cold hardy succulents\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6081\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Put-your-bird-bath-to-a-different-use-by-filling-it-with-succulents-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Put your bird bath to a different use by filling it with succulents\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6091\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Fill-a-bird-bath-with-succulents-to-create-a-fun-piece-of-garden-decor-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Fill a bird bath with succulents to create a fun piece of garden decor\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I'm loving how this turned out, plus it makes a great early birthday gift for my mom! Hopefully this inspires you to add some extra fun to your garden decor. Have you filled a bird bath with succulents? If so I'd love to see it!<\/p>\n<h4>UPDATE: See how this succulent filled bird bath survived and what I did to help it thrive in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/tips-planting-succulents-bird-bath\/\">this post<\/a>.<\/h4>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-2 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":fa